We’re using Talon SRX controllers for our off season project but I’m having some issues with the vendor dependency. Pheonix v6 doesn’t support Talon SRX and wpilib doesn’t support v5 as its from 2023 not 2024. Do I need to downgrade my wpilib as well?

Vendor Dependency CTRE-Phoenix (v5) has invalid year 2023. Expected to be 2024. Reach out to the vendor to get a new version of the dependency. Attempting to modify an existing dependency will break at runtime, and will result in loss of support 
from the WPILib team

You need to use the 2024 phoenix 5 vendordep:

Phoenix 6

Installing Phoenix 6 (FRC)

Java/C++ Offline Download the Phoenix Framework Installer, Navigate through the installer, ensuring applicable options are selected. Showing the installation screen root Apply the vendordep via WPI...

The installer installs both v5 and v6 for offline use, and the link for the v5 vendordep json for online installation is on that page under “online”
